    implementation_delta: |
      Cycle 011: LNG-CORE-59 completed - List slicing operator [start:end:step].
      
      Implementation:
      - Added slice node validation to runtime/ast_contract.py
        - Validates target, start, end, step fields
        - Accepts null for optional bounds
      - Runtime slice evaluation already implemented in interpreter_runtime.py
        - Python-style slicing with negative indices support
        - Optional start/end bounds (defaults to 0/len)
        - Step parameter with positive and negative values
        - Bounds clamping to list size
        - Zero step detection (raises E_RT_SLICE_STEP_ZERO)
        - Type checking for list targets and int bounds
      - Created runtime/test_list_slicing_manual.py with 13 comprehensive tests
      
      Test Results: 13/13 passed
      - Basic positive indices [1:3]
      - Negative start [-2:]
      - Negative end [:-1]
      - Step parameter [::2]
      - Reverse slicing [::-1]
      - Empty slice [2:2]
      - Out of bounds clamping
      - Zero step error
      - Non-list target error
      - Non-int bound error
      - Full copy [:]
      - Both negative indices [-3:-1]
      - Start > end (empty result)
    tests:
      - runtime/test_list_slicing_manual.py: 13/13 pass
    changed_files:
